\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \strokec2 When the storm finally passed, the villagers came together to thank Lars. They realized that it wasn't just the bread that had nourished them, but the love and kindness with which it was given. From that day on, Lars was not just a baker to them, but a friend, a confidant, and a beacon of hope.
\f1\fs24 \
